		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			This spell apparently increases in power as you increase in level,<BR>
but since I'm only level 12 at the moment I don't know is there is<BR>
an upper limit to to it.  When I first got it it did 46 points of damage,<BR>
and now it's doing 48.<BR>
<BR>
A good strategy to use with this spell, which is excellent for hunting animals<BR>
in the wild, is to target your subject at a great distance, hit it with Fire Bolt, and when it comes running toward you, cast root so that it stops before it gets to you and then the rest shout be obvious.  Dealing out 46+ points of fire damage per cast, it is very<BR>
rare to find things that will break free of the rooting spell before you have used up all your manna by roasting it with fire bolt after fire bolt.  I have had no problems killing the larger<BR>
wild animals, like bears, young kodiaks, pumas, and lions.<BR>
<BR>
Of course, if something *does* break free once you're out of manna, you know the drill.  (Run like heck.)
			</font>
	
